    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;evocation&nbsp;[light];\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;adept 3, cleric/oracle 3, inquisitor 3, occultist 2, psychic 3, sorcerer/wizard 2;\n    \n    <strong>Subdomain</strong>&nbsp;Day 2;\n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;1 standard action<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, M (ruby dust worth 50 gp)<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    \n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;object touched Effect magical, heatless flame<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;permanent<br>\n      <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;none;&nbsp;\n      <strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>A flame, equivalent in brightness to a torch, springs forth from an object that you touch. The effect looks like a regular flame, but it creates no heat and doesn't use oxygen. A <i>continual flame</i> can be covered and hidden but not smothered or quenched.</p><p>Light spells counter and dispel <i>darkness</i> spells of an equal or lower level.</p>\n</div>\n",
